sentences: Don McCarlos (born Euvin Spencer, 29 June 1952), is a Jamaican reggae singer and composer.
Don Carlos began singing in 1973 as a member of Black Uhuru.
In 1988 he recorded "Jingle Bells" with Glenice Spenser on A Reggae Christmas on RAS Records.

In 1990 he re-united as the lead vocalist for a Black Uhuru album.
Carlos performed in Nairobi, Kenya in 2010 and on June 3, 2017.
